• [Wikipedia:History of Wikipedian processes and people](/Wikipedia:History_of_Wikipedian_processes_and_people)  

• Creating new project pages  

• Further information: [Wikipedia:Avoid writing redundant essays](/Wikipedia:Avoid_writing_redundant_essays) and [Wikipedia:Content_forking/Internal § Policy forks](/Wikipedia:Content_forking/Internal)  

• See also: [Wikipedia:User pages§What may I have in my user pages?](/Wikipedia:User_pages), and [Wikipedia:Drafts§Creating and editing drafts](/Wikipedia:Drafts)  

• [Shortcut](/Wikipedia:Shortcut)  

• • WP:PRJCRE[WP:PRJCRE](/Wikipedia:PRJCRE)  

• Essays and information pages may be established by writing them and adding {{[Essay](/Template:Essay)}}, {{[Information page](/Template:Information_page)}}, {{[Wikipedia how-to](/Template:Wikipedia_how-to)}}, or [similar templates](/Wikipedia:Template_messages/Wikipedia_namespace) to the page. Essays and information pages in the "Wikipedia namespace" should not be used to create an alternative rule set. Creation of new guideline and policy pages require discussion and a [high level of consensus](/Wikipedia:Local_consensus) from the entire community before publication (see [WP:PROPOSAL](/Wikipedia:PROPOSAL) for procedural details). For general recommendations about the creation and improvement of existing guideline and policy pages, see [Wikipedia:Policy writing is hard](/Wikipedia:Policy_writing_is_hard).  

• The project namespace contains many pages and a lot of information. Try to avoid creating new pages unnecessarily. Before creating a new page, you should consider looking through the [topical index](/Wikipedia:Editor%27s_index_to_Wikipedia), [essay directory](/Wikipedia:Essay_directory) and [help directory](/Help:Directory) to see if the material belongs at a page that already exists. It is strongly recommended that you propose a [WikiProject](/Wikipedia:PJ) at the [proposal page](/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Council/Proposals), if there are enough willing editors to participate in the project. Already existing WikiProjects can be found in the [directory of WikiProjects](/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Council/Directory).  

• Deletion of project pages  

• • Main page: [Wikipedia:Miscellany for deletion](/Wikipedia:Miscellany_for_deletion)  

• • See also: [Wikipedia:User pages§Deletion of user pages](/Wikipedia:User_pages), and [Wikipedia:Drafts§Deleting a draft](/Wikipedia:Drafts)  

• [Shortcut](/Wikipedia:Shortcut)  

• • WP:PRJDEL[WP:PRJDEL](/Wikipedia:PRJDEL)  

• If editing can improve the page, this should be done rather than deleting the page. Disputes over page content are usually not dealt with by deleting the page, except in severe cases. The content issues should be discussed at the relevant talk page, and other methods of [dispute resolution](/Wikipedia:Resolving_disputes) should be used first, such as listing on ["requests for comments"](/Wikipedia:Requests_for_comments) for further input. If a project page clearly satisfies a "general" [speedy deletion criterion](/Wikipedia:CSD), it should be tagged with the [appropriate template](/Wikipedia:GCSD).  

• The usual deletion process is to post a request at [miscellany for deletion](/Wikipedia:MFD) to have project pages [deleted](/Wikipedia:Deletion_policy). Make sure that a notice of the request is posted to the talk page of the affected project. If the project is under a parent WikiProject, a notice should be posted there as well.  

• Essays, information pages, and other informal pages that are only supported by a small minority of the community may be moved to the [primary author's userspace](/Wikipedia:Userfication) over deletion. The Wikipedia community has historically tolerated a wide range of Wikipedia related subjects and viewpoints on [user pages](/Wikipedia:User_pages).  

• It is generally preferable that [inactive WikiProjects](/Wikipedia:Inactive_WikiProjects) not be deleted, but instead be marked as {{[WikiProject status](/Template:WikiProject_status)|inactive}}, or redirected to a relevant WikiProject, or changed to a task force of a parent WikiProject, unless the WikiProject was incompletely created or is entirely undesirable. See [WP:INACTIVEWP](/Wikipedia:INACTIVEWP) for more details.  

• Policies, guidelines and process pages  

• Further information: [Wikipedia:Village pump (policy)](/Wikipedia:Village_pump_(policy))  

• Policies, guidelines and process pages should not be nominated for deletion, as such nominations will probably be considered [disruptive](/Wikipedia:Do_not_disrupt_Wikipedia_to_illustrate_a_point), and the ensuing discussions [closed early](/Wikipedia:Speedy_keep). The {{[Disputed tag](/Template:Disputed_tag)}} template is typically used for claims that an essay, WikiProject advice or information page was recently assigned guideline or policy status without [proper or sufficient consensus](/Wikipedia:PROPOSAL) being established. See [WP:Local consensus](/Wikipedia:Local_consensus) for more details.  

• Copyright violations  

• • Main page: [Wikipedia:Text copyright violations 101](/Wikipedia:Text_copyright_violations_101)  

• If the entire project page is a copyright violation, nominate it for [G12 speedy deletion](/Wikipedia:CSD) with {{[db-copyvio](/Template:Db-copyvio)|url=link to the source text}} . For issues only affecting specific revisions on a page (where other page versions are fine), [revision delete](/Wikipedia:CFRD) is usually more appropriate. To request revision-deletion for copyright violations, see {{[Copyvio-revdel](/Template:Copyvio-revdel)}} for details.  

• Namespace history  

• The Wikipedia namespace began after the January 2002 release of the [Phase II software](/Wikipedia:Phase_II_software). Prior to that, an index of related pages was maintained at Wikipedia utilities , which remained for some time afterwards at Wikipedia:Utilities . This list of pages in the project namespace has been replaced by the pages as described above.  

• Project namespace search  

• • Main page: [Help:Searching§Administrative namespaces](/Help:Searching)  

• By default, [Wikipedia's search engine](/Help:Searching) looks in the Article namespace. To search in the Wikipedia namespace, you would type the project page prefix Wikipedia: ( Wikipedia followed by a colon) or WP: ( WP followed by a colon), followed by some text identifying or relating to the search target. You can also use the [Special:Search](/Special:Search) box below to locate Wikipedia/Project namespace pages. See [Help:Searching](/Help:Searching) for more information.  

• Project namespace banners  

• See [Wikipedia:Template messages/Wikipedia namespace](/Wikipedia:Template_messages/Wikipedia_namespace) for a listing of Wikipedia namespace banners.  

• Notes  

• ^ The {{[Supplement](/Template:Supplement)}} template used for "explanatory essays" is intended as a separate "supplement" banner used for pages derived from policy improvement conversations. The template does not indicate a "higher status" within the community for an essay, but is used to denote that the essay in question has wide acceptance to be linked from said policy or guideline page. See [Template:Supplement](/Template:Supplement) for more information.  

